body:
@chrisduerr 

For me this wrong behaviour hits me immediately when I try to move my cursor back...
It seems to be that regression has been introduced after `a47d716` - so in the `cfc20d4f34`

I've tried adding some debug statements in hope that this might shed some more light on what exactly is going on when the cursor disappears. If someone who's capable of reproducing this reliably could try running this diff and send me the output it would be much appreciated.

<details>

```diff
diff --git a/src/term/mod.rs b/src/term/mod.rs
index 0e95423..ecfb2a4 100644
--- a/src/term/mod.rs
+++ b/src/term/mod.rs
@@ -236,6 +236,7 @@ impl<'a> RenderableCellsIter<'a> {
                 && (cursor.col + 1) < grid.num_cols();
             Some(cursor::get_cursor_glyph(cursor_style, metrics, offset_x, offset_y, is_wide))
         } else {
+            println!("Cursor is hidden: {:?} {:?}", term.mode.contains(TermMode::SHOW_CURSOR), grid.contains(cursor));
             // Use hidden cursor so text will not get inverted
             cursor_style = CursorStyle::Hidden;
             None
@@ -377,6 +378,7 @@ impl<'a> Iterator for RenderableCellsIter<'a> {
             if self.cursor_offset == self.inner.offset() && self.inner.column() == self.cursor.col {
                 // Handle cursor
                 if let Some(cursor_cell) = self.cursor_cell.take() {
+                    println!("Rendering existing cursor glyph with style {:?}", self.cursor_style);
                     let cell = Indexed {
                         inner: self.grid[self.cursor],
                         column: self.cursor.col,
@@ -388,11 +390,13 @@ impl<'a> Iterator for RenderableCellsIter<'a> {
                     renderable_cell.inner = RenderableCellContent::Raw(cursor_cell);
 
                     if let Some(color) = self.config.cursor_cursor_color() {
+                        println!("Overriding cursor cursor color");
                         renderable_cell.fg = color;
                     }
 
                     return Some(renderable_cell);
                 } else {
+                    println!("Rendering content below cursor with style {:?}", self.cursor_style);
                     let mut cell =
                         RenderableCell::new(self.config, self.colors, self.inner.next()?, false);
 
@@ -400,6 +404,7 @@ impl<'a> Iterator for RenderableCellsIter<'a> {
                         std::mem::swap(&mut cell.bg, &mut cell.fg);
 
                         if let Some(color) = self.config.cursor_text_color() {
+                            println!("Overriding cursor text color");
                             cell.fg = color;
                         }
                     }
```

</details>

@chrisduerr I've ran alacritty with your diff. I was able to get the broken cursor behavior, but the output, in the moment of switching to the wrong behavior, was the same as with the 'normal' cursor. Anyway here is the log. I've opened the file with neovim and start moving my cursor down and then up, until I got my cursor inverted, then closed terminal ( when HollowBlock messages appear). 

[log.txt](https://github.com/jwilm/alacritty/files/3109885/log.txt)

I will try to debug it with rr and gdb. I hope that I'll find something.
